-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/knick-great-earl-the-pearl-crusades-for-nutrition-audio-.html
Earl Monroe, New York Knicks Hall of
Fame member, says his diabetes diagnosis led him to join 
drug-giant Merck to campaign for better nutrition. Monroe talks 
with Bloomberg's Ken Prewitt and  Carol Massar  on Bloomberg 
Radio's "Bloomberg Surveillance."     (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 09:35
 